<% content_for :title, "Privacy Policy" %>

<div class="row justify-content-center">
  <div class="col-lg-7">
    <h1 class="h3 fw-bold mb-1">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-muted small mb-4">Last updated: May 2026</p>

    <div class="vstack gap-4">
      <section>
        <h2 class="h5 fw-semibold">What we collect</h2>
        <ul class="text-muted">
          <li><strong>Account:</strong> your email address and a hashed password (or a Google-verified email if you sign in with Google).</li>
          <li><strong>Contacts:</strong> names, email addresses, timezones, preferred hours, and notes you enter for the people you want to stay in touch with.</li>
          <li><strong>Events:</strong> dates, types, titles, and notes for the catch-ups you log.</li>
          <li><strong>Session data:</strong> IP address and user-agent stored temporarily to keep you logged in.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="h5 fw-semibold">How we use it</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">We use your data only to run the Serendipity service. That means showing you who to reach out to and saving a history of your catch-ups. We do not sell or share your data. We do not use it for ads.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="h5 fw-semibold">How to request deletion</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">Want to delete your account? Email us at
          <a href="mailto:stayintouch.cs396@gmail.com">stayintouch.cs396@gmail.com</a>.
          Use the subject line <em>"Delete my account"</em>. We will remove your data within 7 days.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="h5 fw-semibold">Third-party services</h2>
        <p class="text-muted">If you connect Google Calendar, we store an OAuth access token. We use it to write events for you. You can disconnect at any time from the People page. We do not read your existing calendar data.</p>
      </section>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-4"><%= link_to "← Back", :back, class: "text-muted small" %></p>
  </div>
</div>
